@shoxell: I gave my toolchain to two regulars here. Well, there haven't been sudden increase of production - let say it on half-kidding way. It's so simple that confuses people - as you have noticed, my daily production is too huge to tolerate unnecessary waste of time in encoding process - but, in order to be used - my toolchain prefers someone who is very very long in H264 encoding, ahem, ultimately familiar with command line, libx264 internals and targets limitations.

To cut long story short - I am convinced that my toolchain is no better than few other encoding programs. It's true. Maybe it's faster, maybe a little bit better - but mainly because of the direction given by person behind the wheels (me). 

If you want, e-mail me, and I could send you as reply my encoding lines. Just that. Rest of the programs you must get yourself.
